In <43do84$jjn@sake.wwa.com>, nineveh@wwa.com writes:
>>> > Can anybody recommend me a good book on OS/2 programming (for C)?
>
>OS/2 Presentation Manager Programming, by Charles Petzold (believe it or not), is
>a very good book.

I'd recommend OS/2 WARP PROGRAMMING FOR DUMMIES by Blake Watson.  It gets you
started.  The disk of examples is available from the author and does not come with
the book :-(.  It's not as detailed as Petzold but the topics covered are well done.  I'd
recommend this book for the overview of Warp programming and Petzold for the
bible or everything you need to know about Warp programming.
---
