<Sniff sniff>

"Doesn't [sniff] anybody like [sniff sniff] my book anymore? [sniff]"

I spoke with John Wiley and Sons last week and they gave me a date of
September 15 for the release of _The Art of OS/2 Warp Programming_.

Since I don't believe there is any single book that handles everything,
I recommend _The Art of.._, Petzold's book, and _Real World Programming
for OS/2 2.11_ by Blain, Delimon, and English.  If you're looking for a
good design level book, see _Designing High Powered OS/2 Applications_ by
Reich.

Of course, Carsten Whimster has reviewed all of these books for EDM/2.
I'd recommend reading about them there.

